
[1]elopement

   ELO'PEMENT, n. Private or unlicensed departure from the place or
   station to which one is assigned by duty or law; as the elopement of a
   wife from her husband, or of a daughter from her father's house,
   usually with a lover or gallant. It is sometimes applied to the
   departure of a son or an apprentice, in like manner.
